<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/329: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-15T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 15,
                                            1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>For representative of American International Corporation: “Funds
                                provided for by agreement signed July 8th, for second advance Canal
                                survey deposited National City Bank today. Request Legation have
                                Treasury note dated accordingly and to forward immediately via
                                pouch. Telegraph when despatched. Stone.”</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>